author: Written by: Chris Finch, Digital Content Director
title: Several voting locations moving ahead of election
text:
There will be some polling changes in Orleans Parish for the Oct. 24 election.
The Orleans Parish Clerk of Court says six former voting locations will move ahead of the election.
Woodland Presbyterian Church will move to Alice B. Harte Elementary School; Our Lady of the Rosary moves to McDonogh City Park Academy; John Dibert School moves to Pierre Capdua at Thurgood Marshall; St. Peter Claver School moves to St. Peter Claver UJIMA Fern Brady Building; Isidore Newman will move its polling location to the Henson Building on the schoolâ€™s campus; and Kipp Believe College Prep moves its location to Central St. Matthew United Church of Christ.
The Clerk of Court says commissioners will be at the former locations to redirect wayward voters.
